Annotation.note:
A family of systems with symmetry group $C_3$ and common zero
$(1,1,1)$ with $n\geq 2$. 

The ideal generated by these polynomials seems always to have
dimension 0. No obvoius formula for the multiplicity is
known.

It can be generated by the following code:
\begin{verbatim}
#requires System=Maple
polys:=[ x+y*z^n-2, y+z*x^n-2, z+x*y^n-2];

vars:=[x,y,z];
\end{verbatim}

\begin{keywords}
discrete symmetries
\end{keywords}
